## Description {#details}

<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/object/machoabstractfixupentry">MachOAbstractFixupEntry</a> is an abstract class representing a fixup in a MH&#95;DYLDLINK file.

Fixups generally represent rebases and binds. Binds also subdivide into additional subtypes (weak, lazy, reexport).

The two concrete subclasses of <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/object/machoabstractfixupentry">MachOAbstractFixupEntry</a> are:

MachORebaseBindEntry - for dyld opcode-based tables, including threaded- rebase, where rebases are mixed in with other bind opcodes. <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/object/machochainedfixupentry">MachOChainedFixupEntry</a> - for pointer chains embedded in data pages.

Definition at line 322 of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/object/macho-h">MachO.h</a>.
